@NODE CRMFIX
@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}
@{fg shine}crm.library fixer by Zbigniew Trzcionkowski <zeeball@interia.pl>@{fg text}

Patches:

@{B}crm.library 4.11 (04.10.93)@{UB} --> @{B}crm.library 4.11 (01.01.02)@{UB}
@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}

This fix brings you:

- removed patching of (New)LoadSeg - this is obsolete
  and gives opportunity to hide other patches at these
  very vital entrypoints...
  Harddisks are very popular nowdays and there are many
  better ways of decompression... e.g. XFH-handler!

- library finally becomes expungable - I mean that for
  instance 'c:avail flush' restores all memory
  occupied by this library and... that's it!

- maybe optimised speed - I have fixed some labels in
  the library to be longword aligned... :)

- os37+ only library!

@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}

Following steps have to be done for proper installation:
(by clicking they should happen automatically)

1. Make new library file in RAM: depending on the currently installed
   library file. If this step fails it seems that you have to get the
   above mentioned library first...

   @{"spatch -ocrm.library -pcrm.pch libs:crm.library      " SYSTEM "spatch -ocrm.library -pcrm.pch libs:crm.library"}

2. Rename currently installed library to have it's backup!

   @{"rename libs:crm.library libs:crm.library.old         " SYSTEM "rename libs:crm.library libs:crm.library.old"}

3. Copy our patched library to the libs

   @{"copy crm.library to libs:crm.library                 " SYSTEM "copy crm.library to libs:crm.library"}

4. Delete the library file that was created in point 1

   @{"delete crm.library                                   " SYSTEM "delete crm.library"}

@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}

CrunchMania and all accompanied stuff is:

(c) Thomas Schwarz (BTW: this release is based on test
                         version and has nothing to do
                         with the registered product!)

CrM can be obtained from Aminet: @{B}util/pack/CrMv191t.lha@{UB}

@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}

Remember:

Currently the only suggested usage of this library is letting for proper
execution of 'Crm-library' compressed files without getting these nasty
patches. It is suggested just to decrunch files with xfd.

@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}
@ENDNODE
@NODE EXPFIX
@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}
@{fg shine}explode.library fixer by Zbigniew Trzcionkowski <zeeball@interia.pl>@{fg text}

Patches:
@{B}explode.library 5.6.29 (16.7.91)@{UB} -->
                                     --> @{B}explode.library 7.0 (01.01.02)@{UB}
@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}

This fix brings you:

- removed patching of (New)LoadSeg - this is obsolete
  and gives opportunity to hide other patches at these
  very vital entrypoints...
  Harddisks are very popular nowdays and there are many
  better ways of decompression... e.g. XFH-handler!

- library finally becomes expungable - I mean that for
  instance 'c:avail flush' restores all memory
  occupied by this library and... that's it!

- maybe optimised speed - I have fixed some labels in
  the library to be longword aligned... :)

- os37+ only library!

@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}

Following steps have to be done for proper installation:
(by clicking they should happen automatically)

1. Make new library file in RAM: depending on the currently installed
   library file. If this step fails it seems that you have to get the
   above mentioned library first...

   @{"spatch -oexplode.library -pexplode.pch libs:explode.library     " SYSTEM "spatch -oexplode.library -pexplode.pch libs:explode.library"}

2. Rename currently installed library to have it's backup!

   @{"rename libs:explode.library libs:explode.library.old            " SYSTEM "rename libs:explode.library libs:explode.library.old"}

3. Copy our patched library to the libs

   @{"copy ram:explode.library to libs:explode.library                " SYSTEM "copy explode.library to libs:explode.library"}

4. Delete the library file that was created in point 1

   @{"delete explode.library                                          " SYSTEM "delete explode.library"}

@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}

Imploder and all accompanied stuff is:

(c) Peter Struijk and Albert J.Brouwer

Imploder can be obtained from Aminet: @{B}util/pack/imploder_4_0.lzh@{UB}

@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}

Remember:

Currently the only suggested usage of this library is
letting for execution of 'Imploder-library' compressed
files without getting these nasty patches.

@{U}--------------------------------------------------------------------------@{UU}
@ENDNODE
